Sure, Pavan! Here's a simple "Hello, World!" program in C++:

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    std::cout << "Hello, World!" << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

This program includes the `<iostream>` header, which allows you to use the `std::cout` object for output. The `main()` function is where the program starts execution. Inside `main()`, we use `std::cout` to print "Hello, World!" to the console, followed by `std::endl` to move the cursor to the next line.

You can compile and run this program using a C++ compiler like `g++` on your computer. If you need any more details on how to set up a C++ development environment or compile this code, feel free to ask!
